author: Staff Reports
title: Seabury v-ball stops McLouth
text:
Advertisement 
Bishop Seabury Academy swept McLouth, 25-15, 25-12, 25-16, in high school volleyball Thursday at Seabury. 
The Seahawks were led by Taylor Hodge with seven kills, four aces and 10 digs, Ellen Almanza with six kills and 16 digs, Lindsey Hornberger with eight kills, two aces, five digs and one block, Regan Zaremba with two kills, three aces, 30 assists and six digs, Celia Taylor-Puckett with four kills and nine digs, and Vivian Aubel with seven kills, 10 aces and nine digs. 
Seabury (17-9) will play Saturday in the Wellsville Tournament.
